Text.string: Hey. Can you, uh, track somethin' down for me?
Ugh. This place is a mess.
Is it safe yet? I can hear you out there!
Hello? Terry? Is it safe?
Uh, Terry? I'm running out of food in here! Can you let me out yet?
What's happening out there, Terry?
You aren't Terry! Where is he? What have you done to Terry?! He's supposed to let me out when it's safe!
Is Terry keeping you prisoner?
Did this Terry guy kidnap you?
Are you a captive against your will?
Uh, has this Terry fella been keepin' you prisoner?
The receptionist's desk should have a door unlock button. Give that a go.
Hey, who's in there?
Hello? Who's in there?
Who are you?
Oi! Who's hidin' in there?
Okay! I hope this keyboard does all the work and I don't have to shove this brain in manually.
Uh, okay—I'm just going to mash on this keyboard and hope the whole brain-transfer-thing works out automatically.
I will now merge man and beast with the press of a button!
So just press a button and it goes right in? Nice and easy. Not like it's brain surgery or anythin'.

What? No-no-no-no, he locked me in here to keep me safe from the others! He was gonna let me out once the coast was clear but it's been a while. Man, I hope he's okay. Could YOU get me out of here? The door controls are on the other side of that glass.
Those ratches are murder-crazy! You gotta kill 'em before I come out!
Yeah, right there! That's the door control!
Oh man, it feels so good to be out of there. Come say hi!

Ever since the attack, I've been seeing ratch all over Atlas! My janitor Terry is supposed to be taking care of it, but no one's seen him! Go find Terry and get him back to work. Check his office first.
Hold on, wait. You're a ratch.
Uh... you're a ratch.
I am confused. You are a ratch?
Hot damn, fella! You're a ratch!
Yup! Thanks to my main man Terry! He saved my life! Come on, we gotta find him!
Ah, no! Terry! They got him!
Okay, but actually, what's going on?
Right, tell me what's going on right now, or I'm just gonna start punching.
One moment. Please explain, just... your whole deal.
Hold up. What the actual feck is happenin' here?
Ugh! Boy! Terry really lives like an animal. Look around, maybe he left like a day planner or something. Not that he really seems like a... day planner kind of guy.
Terry was my best bud. When my human body got sick, he vowed to save me! He took some ECHOnet courses and found this lab, and pretty soon he figured out how to transfer human brains to ratch bodies.
All these other ratches here are escaped failed experiments. Terry had to test the brain transfer process before he tried it on me, so he used bandits and captured Maliwan soldiers.
Quick—our only chance to save Terry is to get his brain into a ratch body! I'll chew it out!
[chewing noises]
Please don't—you're already eating him. Okay.
No-no-no, you don't have to—oh, yep, it's happening.
Would it not be simpler—ah, no. The feast has already begun.
Could you wait—oh, okay, okay, no, no. You're eating your friend. Good. Perfect.
Now grab his brain, so we can bring him back to life!
Great! The brain transfer tank is downstairs. Agh, but Gary's cage is in the way. Hey Gary!
There's gotta be a clue in there somewhere.
Rrgh! I'm gonna eat your face! I'll wear your mom's skin as a kimono! I'll feed your kids to you!
Haha! Classic Gary. Maliwan war criminal. Honestly, I think he ate people BEFORE he got ratch'd up. Flip that switch to drop his cage so we can get to the transfer tank!
Rrgh, I'm free! I'll guzzle your soul-milk! I'll break your toenails! I'll—I'll spoonfeed you your own tongue!
Hey, Gary got out! I'm gonna stay up here, and... maybe you... go kill him and do the brain transfer thing.
Hey, Gary's dead! Awesome. Now go put Terry's brain into the transfer tank! Time lost is Terry lost!
All right, there's already a fresh ratch body in there! I don't know how Terry gets the ratch brain out, but I did see him sharpening an ice cream scoop the other day.
Now pull that lever and we'll get Terry back!
Ugh... yagh! Agahghh!
Terry, it's Glenn! Can you understand me?
Maybe... look behind stuff? I know I always hide clues to my location behind random stuff. It's a nervous habit.
Rgrhhh! Aghgh, ghhh...
He's just having some trouble adjusting. Try talking to him, remind him that he's a human in there.
Um. Hey, man. Sometimes life is like... a ratch. And you're a ratch now. So... that's how you know you're alive. I guess.
Uh, listen up. You're better than this. You're not just a ratch. You're... Terry, and you are ALIVE!
You there. Form is meaningless—it is what you DO with that form. You are no ratch. You are Terry!
Heyyyy, boyo. So, long story, you're a ratch now, and you've got to live with that. Get over it.
Ughaghhh! Ughh... alive! I... Glenn? I'm alive! And I'm a ratch! You brought me back! I'm ALIVE!
Terry! We did it, buddy! We survived!

Okay! So I finally found the little rubber thing that goes on your thumb and you are not gonna believe where—WOAH, talking ratch. I am NOT caught up on this. Actually, you know what. Don't tell me. Plausible deniability. I'm just going to... do some CEO stuff and look the other way.
Hey, rescuer—I got a thank you present for ya.
We found that cool Atlas weapon prototype when we moved into the lab. But it only works with, you know, hands and stuff. So enjoy!
Glenn, you did it! You brought me back!
Hell yeah, man! I wasn't gonna leave you dead on the floor! Oh, right, I kinda ate your body, man. Sorry.
A secret door? Terry's a janitor, what secrets does he need to keep? Ach, oh, don't answer that. Every possible answer is gross.
No, no, I totally get it. I could actually super go for a human body right now.
Ratch pals for life, man!
Ratch pals for life!
Hey! What's up?
Oh, that's one of the old skunkworks labs! Yeah, I shut it down after all the... accidents.

I said that all spooky, but it was just a lot of papercuts. Promethea's healthcare system is a nightmare. It was just cheaper to shut down the lab. I'm nervous about papercuts now, keep looking around while I go find my little rubber fingerguards.
Terry? Terry, is that you?
